    <item>
      <title>Quickly generate RGB codes</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/my-first-post/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 09 May 2022 20:05:11 +0300</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/my-first-post/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I needed to quickly generate a bunch of RGB hex codes. I also needed them to be available in the clipboard.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The best solution that I could find was to use &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/sharkdp/pastel&#34;&gt;pastel&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The magic command is the following.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-fallback&#34; data-lang=&#34;fallback&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;pastel random -n 1 | pastel format | xclip -sel clip&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now put on a keybind, with something like i3 and you have a handy code at the stroke of a few buttons.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
